term_inventory_greek.meaning:
life, soul; heart, mind; a person; the immaterial (and eternal) part of inner person, often meaning the animate self, which can be translated by pronouns: 'my soul' = 'I, myself'
breath; the principle of animal life;
the life (Mt 2:20; 6:25; Mk 3:4; Lk 21:19; Jn 10:11);
an inanimate being (1Cor 15:45); a human individual, soul (Acts 2:41; 3:23; 7:14; 27:37; Rom 13:1; 1Pet 3:20);
the immaterial soul (Mt 10:28; 1Pet 1:9; 2:11, 25; 4:19);
the soul, heart as the seat of religious and moral sentiment (Mt 11:29; Acts 14:2, 22; 15:24; Eph 6:6);
the soul as a seat of feeling (Mt 12:18; 26:38);
the soul, the inner self (Lk 12:19)

STEP sub-gloss facets (same lexeme, G5590):
  G-suffix: soul (core inner self/heart)
  H-suffix: soul: life (psuchē as animate life)
  I-suffix: soul: myself (psuchē as reflexive self/pronoun)
  J-suffix: soul: person (psuchē as countable individual)
  K-suffix: soul: animal (psuchē applied to non-human animate life)
